'''Bus-Tops''' was a project for the [[Cultural Olympiad|2012 Cultural Olympiad]], part of the Artists Taking The Lead project funded by [[Arts Council England]] and in collaboration with [[LOCOG]].<ref>{{cite news
|url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-16510085
|title = London 2012: Olympic-inspired art to light up bus stops
|first = Jenny 
|last = Minard
|date = 11 January 2012
|work = [[BBC News]]
}}</ref>

Bus-Tops saw a series of 30 red LED screens situated on the roofs of bus stops in 20 London boroughs displaying art work made by both the public and established artists.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/what-we-do/our-priorities-2011-15/london-2012/artists-taking-the-lead/| title=Artists taking the lead| publisher=Arts Council England| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150325155959/http://www.artscouncil.org.uk/what-we-do2/our-priorities-2011-15/london-2012/artists-taking-the-lead/| archive-date=25 March 2015| dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=http://festival.london2012.com/about/culturalolympiad/artists-taking-the-lead.php| title=Artists Taking the Lead| website=festival.london2012.com| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120529213647/http://festival.london2012.com/about/culturalolympiad/artists-taking-the-lead.php| archive-date=29 May 2012| dead-url=yes}}</ref> The screens were powered by [[Beagle Board]]s running custom software and [[3G]] connections to receive art content and upload sensor-based information. The installations were fed art content via the project's website where anyone could upload artwork to be considered for inclusion on a screen.<ref>{{cite video
|url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/programmes/click_online/9692525.stm
|title = bus-tops.com
|publisher = [[BBC News]], [[Click (TV programme)|Click]]
|date=February 2012

}} (video, index: 03:35)</ref>

The project was scheduled to end at the end of the Olympic period, 30 September 2012.

